radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal atelectasis in the visualized lung bases. No pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation with no focal lesions. The pancreas is normal without focal lesions. The spleen shows normal size. The kidneys are normal with a small left renal hypodensity likely a cyst. The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated to approximately 1.4 cm with periappendiceal fat stranding and appendicoliths. No evidence of perforation. No free fluid in the pelvis. A retroflexed uterus with a 2.6 cm cyst in the left ovary.
